# Finding 061
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Repeated `readSource` helper in view/client-element tests
- File + line(s): `apps/jskit-value-app/tests/views/consoleAiTranscriptsView.vitest.js:9-11`, `apps/jskit-value-app/tests/views/consoleMembersView.vitest.js:9-11`, `apps/jskit-value-app/tests/views/workspaceMembersView.vitest.js:9-11`, `apps/jskit-value-app/tests/views/workspaceTranscriptsView.vitest.js:10-12`, `packages/ai-agent/assistant-transcript-explorer-client-element/test/AssistantTranscriptExplorerClientElement.vitest.js:13-15`, `packages/observability/console-errors-client-element/test/ConsoleErrorsClientElement.vitest.js:13-15`, `packages/users/members-admin-client-element/test/MembersAdminClientElement.vitest.js:11-13`
- Why it can drift/fail: A tiny file-reading helper is redefined in multiple tests; if the approach changes (encoding, path resolution), every test needs manual updates.
- Concrete impact: Boilerplate creep and inconsistent test setup changes.
- Exact remediation: Add a shared `readSource` test helper (e.g., `tests/helpers/readSource.js`) and import it where needed.

## Resolution
- Justification: This is client-side view/client-element test code, and client templates/tests are being actively rewritten; per instruction, defer client-side work.
- Revisit signal: Once client test scaffolding stabilizes, consolidate `readSource` into a shared test helper and update the tests.
